      <bioghist id="aspace_a59061bcb550d89548a61f83ed650d27">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>Adolph Knopf (1882-1966): on staff of U.S. Geological Survey from 1906-1945; professor of geology at Yale University, 1920-1951; professor emeritus from 1951; author of various books and articles.</p>  
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_542efad19fe2a1fc453d131c73021064">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The major part of the papers consists of reports and maps on the holdings of the Rochester Mines Company in Humboldt County, Nevada (1916-1917). During this period Knopf was on the staff of the U.S. Geological Survey. Also a small amount of professional correspondence and lecture notes, chiefly relating to his career as a professor of geology at Yale University. Eleven of the letters are from Charles Schuchert, a colleague in the department.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
