            <scopecontent id="aspace_5548deeabd8ccae075a22c76a8677e46">
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
               <p>The Adolph Knopf Papers are mostly records of a group of silver mines in Nevada. Knopf's own connection with these is not clear, though a few of the materials seem to bear his annotations. The correspondence consists of letters to and from Charles Schuchert, one carbon copy of a letter to N. L. Bowen, donated by Mrs. Adolph Knopf in May 1972; and copies of correspondence with the Calaveras County Department of Mines and Mining, San Andreas, California, received from the Calaveras Heritage Council in May 1977. The donor of the rest of the material is unknown.</p>
            </scopecontent>
